  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The Loft Conversion with the Rear Dormer by reason of the lack of set back of the rear dormer (above the outrigger) by 20 cm metres from the eaves fails to comply with Class B ,Condition (b)(i) (bb) and the extending upwards of the flank wall by 0.5metres would be at two storey level fails to comply with Class A (extensions). The proposal therefore exceeds the permitted development tolerances set out in Schedule 2, Part 1, Classes A & B of the Town & Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended). Planning permission would therefore be required.\r\n\r\n",
    "Reason : 2 - INFORMATIVE\r\nNote to Applicant\r\nIn accordance with paragraph 38 of the NPPF 2021, The London Borough of Merton  (LBM) takes a positive and proactive approach to development proposals focused on solutions. LBM works with applicants/agents in a positive and proactive manner by:\r\n\"Offering a pre-application advice and duty desk service. \r\n\"Where possible, suggesting solutions to secure a successful outcome.\r\n\"As appropriate, updating applicants/agents of any issues that may arise in the processing of their application.\r\nIn this instance:\r\n\"The application was considered to be fundamentally contrary to the provisions of Classes B and A, Part 1 of Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development Order) 2015 (as amended) there were not considered to be any solutions to resolve this conflict. \r\n"
  ],
